==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Menaccanite
<hw>Me*nac"can*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<etsep>Menaccan</etsep>, in Cornwall, where it was first found.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>An iron-black or steel-gray mineral, consisting
chiefly of the oxides of iron and titanium. It is commonly massive, but
occurs also in rhombohedral crystals. Called also <altname>titanic iron
ore</altname>, and <altname>ilmenite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Menace</ent>⟦br⟧
